                                    <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-chapter-head">[Belgium]</head>
                                    <opener>
                                        <dateline rendition="#right">[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-volume-rules" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1873-12-01T23:59:59-04:56" notBefore="1873-01-01T00:00:00-04:56">undated</date>.]</dateline>
                                    </opener>
                                    <p>The law of Belgium is the same as that of France, except that
                                        the “grande natural isation” can only be conferred by act of
                                        the legislature.<note n="2" xml:id="d214fn2">Ibid. <ref target="frus1873p1v1#pg_53">p. 53</ref>. Letter from
                                            Mr. <persName>Prevost</persName>. Swiss
                                        consul.</note></p>
